# API Error Handling And Observability

- Do not swallow exceptions.
- Return standardized error contracts (`ProblemDetails`).
- Include correlation/trace IDs in logs and responses.
- Use structured logging with contextual properties.

## Good pattern

```csharp
try
{
    // business flow
}
catch (DomainException ex)
{
    _logger.LogWarning(ex, "Domain failure {@CorrelationId}", correlationId);
    return Problem(title: "Domain validation failed", statusCode: 400);
}
```
